@Node "Woz.doc"

Well have you worked with Macintrash-Computers ?? Well the System-Folder
has a nice feature, it seems to know, where some files have to be placed,
like the control-panels and the system-extentions.
SSF does the same. SSF has a DataBase in which file-endings are defined
and a place, where a file with this file-ending will be put.
Like you want all files, which end with .gif should be copied to work:pix.
This program should be used with DirOpus4.1(or higher) or any other
directory utility.

Future versions are planned as device, which you can use with crunchers
or stuff like that. Remember a file containing differend pictures in
different formtas ... now if you lha -r x MyFile.lha SSF: .....


NOTE: At the moment SSF does only recognize files by their ending, like
      .gif, .lha .... in furure versions it is planned do expand the
      search patterns with wildcards.
@EndNode

